history.content:
See @12406 for general answers to your questions, and https://piazza.com/class/hyq0br1u3kx7dg?cid=12406_f1 for answers to your EE120-related questions.

Concurrent EE120 would be better than no EE120, but still wouldn't help you with the first half of the class, where the most EE120-related knowledge is needed.

Hi everyone!

On HKN website, EE120 is listed as a prerequisite for EE C145B. Has anyone taken this class without EE120? Would taking EE120 concurrently be helpful? What exactly from EE120 is needed for this course in case that I could go over the material before classes start?

And overall, what are the experiences about EE145B in terms of workload, structure and quality of the class?

Thank you all!
